{{nihongo|'''Espio the Chameleon'''|<U+30A8><U+30B9><U+30D4><U+30AA><U+30FB><U+30B6><U+30FB><U+30AB><U+30E1><U+30EC><U+30AA><U+30F3>|Esupio za Kamereon}}<ref name="sega"/> is a fictional character in [[Sega]]'s ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (series)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' series of [[video game]]s. He was created for ''[[Knuckles' Chaotix]]'' and demonstrated the technical capabilites of the [[Sega 32X]]. He is a 16-year-old [[anthropomorphism|anthropomorphic]] purple [[chameleon]] with a cool but arrogant personality. He is one-third of the [[List of recurring characters from Sonic the Hedgehog (games)#Chaotix|Chaotix]] team of private investigators.

Espio debuted as a [[player character]] in ''Knuckles' Chaotix'', teaming up with [[Knuckles the Echidna]] and other characters to defeat [[Doctor Ivo Robotnik|Doctor Eggman]]. He is also playable in ''[[Sonic the Fighters]]'', ''[[Sonic Heroes]]'', and ''[[Sonic Rivals 2]]'', and makes [[non-player character|non-playable]] appearances in other games. He is a recurring character in the [[comic book]] series ''[[Sonic the Comic]]'' and ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (comics)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]'', as well as the ''[[Sonic X]]'' anime. He has seen limited inclusion in ''Sonic'' merchandise. He has been generally well-received by critics such as ''[[Mega Zone]]'' and ''[[Sega Saturn Magazine|Sega Magazine]]''.

==Design and characteristics==
Espio was created by [[Sonic Team]] for the video game ''[[Knuckles' Chaotix]]'', as part of the newly introduced [[List of recurring characters from Sonic the Hedgehog (games)#Chaotix|Chaotix]] team of private investigators. In this game, Espio's color subtly changes while he moves, which demonstrated the technical capabilities of the [[Sega 32X]] console.<ref name="xboxworld"/> Espio was incorporated into ''[[Sonic Heroes]]'' as part of a move to reintroduce neglected characters, and because the development team considered him to have a unique, interesting personality.<ref>{{cite web|title=Afterthoughts: Sonic Heroes|url=http://www.1up.com/do/feature?cId=3116996|publisher=[[1UP.com]]|accessdate=May 9, 2010}}</ref> In this game, he was the designated "speed" character while teammates [[Vector the Crocodile (character)|Vector the Crocodile]] and [[List of recurring characters from Sonic the Hedgehog (games)#Charmy Bee|Charmy Bee]] respectively represented "power" and "flight".<ref name="profiles"/> 

Espio's design is that of a 16-year-old [[anthropomorphism|anthropomorphic]] purple [[chameleon]] who stands at 110 cm (3' 7.3") and 36 kg (79.4 lbs).<ref name="sega">{{cite web|title=<U+30A8><U+30B9><U+30D4><U+30AA><U+30FB><U+30B6><U+30FB><U+30AB><U+30E1><U+30EC><U+30AA><U+30F3>|publisher=[[Sega]]|url=http://sonic.sega.jp/SonicChannel/chara/espio/index.html|language=Japanese|accessdate=June 1, 2010}}</ref> He is cool-headed, not threatened by danger,<ref name="profiles">{{cite web|title=Sonic Heroes Profiles: Team Chaotix|url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/444/444347p1.html|date=December 4, 2003|last=Dunham|first=Jeremy|authorlink=Jeremy Dunham|publisher=[[IGN]]|accessdate=May 6, 2010}}</ref> and disciplined, but often arrogant and opinionated.<ref name="heroesmanual">''[[Sonic Heroes]]'' (GameCube) instruction manual, p. 12.</ref> Claustrophobia is his main weakness.<ref name="fighters">{{cite web|title=Gems Collection: The Fighters|url=http://cube.ign.com/articles/639/639843p2.html|publisher=IGN|date=August 5, 2005|last=Castro|first=Juan|accessdate=May 9, 2010}}</ref> Due to his training as a [[ninja]] and his ability to turn [[invisibility|invisible]] at will, he is able to move unnoticed.<ref name="profiles"/> He can move on ceilings and walls.<ref>{{cite web|title=Knuckles Chaotix Review|url=http://screwattack.com/videos/Knuckles-Chaotix-Review-1|publisher=[[ScrewAttack]]|date=December 30, 2009|accessdate=May 3, 2010}}</ref>

